content:
Leon the Professional has everything needed to make a film great:
A fantastic script with many memorable quotes; perfect, stand out performances from all star including Jean Reno, Natalie Portman, Gary Oldman and Danny Aeilo;
humour when needed which can either make a chuckle of straight up belly laugh and even eye catching cinematography.I was this film when I was a young teen but it didn't change my view in the film, of course it's violent and very bleak sometimes but it's not that kind of gore and violence that changes the mood and makes it less enjoyable to watch. I think this film can't be topped. A tragedy that this film didn't even score an Oscar, Golden Globe or BAFTA nomination because I think it deserved to be up there with the greats even it was the year of Pulp Fiction, Forest Gump and the Shawshank Redemption. It's hard to compare but don't shy away from this under appreciated, cinematic masterpiece because it could just change your life.
